I read the reviews here prior to making. My philosophy on cooking is you must adapt everything in order to make the dish your own. I did half balsamic vinegar and half sherry. Made a nice vinegrette. Added capers, roasted red peppers, feta cheese w/ tomato & basil, artichoke hearts (don't think this added anything), fresh chopped parsley, pepperconi, capers (loved these!) and asparagus. This salad would have needed more color from the original hence why I added the green aspargus (perfect for Spring/Summer!), but broccoli or zucchini would have worked too. Would have done the mushrooms as suggested but thought this would be too much and the color wouldn't work too well. I also marinated everything together to help the flavors meld. A couple hours is good, but overnight is even better. This dish made a lot especially when I served it on a bed of mixed greens. It was a big hit at the picnic I attended. Didn't take too much work either.

