Wonderful flavor. Very pretty. I doubled it for a pot lock at work. Everyone went back for seconds & thirds. Even during dessert, they took another helping of the salad. I did the first stage the night before. When mostly cooled I mixed the garlic in a little olive oil and added it early (to give it time to blend & mellow). Next day I did the rest of the second stage just prior to serving. I rougly chopped most of the pinenuts so they would stick to the pasta & fork (otherwise they end up left behind on the plate). Unlike one reviewer, my pasta did not turn too brown from the balsamic, it turned an attractive autumny color that complemented the other colors perfectly. This would also be beautiful in small lettuce leaf cups as an appetizer.

